-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Canadian Western Bank, National Bank of Canada
-- 
-- Thu Aug 28, 2014 06:51AM EDT
-- None



Aug 28 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Canadian Western Bank and National Bank of Canada, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS  * National Bank of Canada <NA.TO>: CIBC ups to sector performer from sector underperformer   * Canadian Western Bank <CWB.TO>: Credit Suisse, RBC raise target price on the stock * Petroamerica Oil Corp <PTA.V>: TD Securities cuts to buy from action list buy  Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Arcan Resources Ltd <ARN.V>: RBC cuts target price to C$0.35 from C$0.50; sector perform * Canacol Energy Ltd <CNE.TO>: TD Securities raises to action list buy from buy * Canacol Energy Ltd <CNE.TO>: TD Securities raises target price to C$12 from C$11.50 * Canadian Western Bank <CWB.TO>: Credit Suisse raises target to C$47 from C$45; neutral * Canadian Western Bank <CWB.TO>: RBC raises target price to C$43 from C$40; sector perform * Knight Therapeutics <GUD.TO>: NBF starts with outperform; price target C$6.50 * National Bank of Canada <NA.TO>: Credit Suisse raises target to C$55 from C$50; neutral * National Bank of Canada <NA.TO>: CIBC ups to sector performer from sector underperformer * National Bank of Canada <NA.TO>: CIBC raises target price to C$54 from C$51 * National Bank Of Canada <NA.TO>: Barclays raises target to C$53 from C$50; equal weight * National Bank Of Canada <NA.TO>: RBC raises target price to C$53 from C$48; sector perform